orgchart.tip.helper.n2won1:
N-2 w/o N-1
Add the missing reporting line for the N-2. Many thanks!
orgchart.tip.helper.n2less:
Missing N-2
There are less than 10 executives in N-2 in that org chart. We should be able to do better!
orgchart.tip.helper.n2miss:
Missing N-2
Our N-2 executives are less than 2 times our N-1 executives. A better ratio should be 3 to 4 times. Many thanks!
orgchart.tip.helper.crawler.tools.urls.l:
Collector URLS
Red - URL cannot be crawled >>> Check if correct
Orange - Page was downloaded over 4 months ago. >>> Check if active
Blue - Page downloaded less 3 month ago and validated by you in the collector. Congrats !
Press Release URLs:
Red - URL could not download or error happening during download. >>> Check URL
Orange - URL could no more download. >>> Check URL
Blue - URL downloaded less 10 days ago = Great! >>> Check if its content is still relevant. Many thanks!
orgchart.tip.helper.twitter.info:
Companies Twitter ID exists:
Green - OK
Orange - only Super Mother Company Twitter exist
Red - no twitters for company AND for Super Mother company.
Tip: All listed companies should have their Twitter handle. Many thanks!
orgchart.tip.helper.ma.news.info:
M&A Status:
Green(complete cycle) : M&A or Bankruptcy
Red (Unclosed) : M&A or Bankruptcy were announced but we did not report the closing/termination.
The same will soon be shown for the IPO and the name changes.
orgchart.tip.helper.stock.ticker.info:
Company Stock Ticker:
Green - Stock ticker exists
Red - No Stock Ticker.
orgchart.tip.helper.delta.diff.days:
Number of days between the less and most recent updates
Grey = 20 - 40 days
Red = 40+ days
orgchart.tip.helper.less.recent.updates:
Last update of the less recent update
Grey = 60 - 100 days = OK
Red = 100+ days = Worth checking !
orgchart.tip.helper.kpi.rating:
Blue = OK !
Red is either because the CEO has no bio,
the company is in a list (missing CEO/Board, N-1 or N-2),
the company is a sub of a company in a list (Missing CEO/Board ot N-1).
>>>All the details in the pop up.
orgchart.subsidiary.tree.tip.company.lin:
Blue if all companies are less than 100 days.
Red if one company is over 100 days.
